<p>3. On the same day The Express has a further story about an Australian (Robert Burgess) who married a British woman ten weeks ago and has now been asked to leave Britain.</p>

<p>4. The case is said to involve considerable hardship for the British wife, and a Home Office spokesman is quoted as saying that a different decision could well be made if there were such hardship for the wife.</p>

<p>4. The Express also contains a selection of letters from readers supporting the Aitken article, as well as an editorial demanding that the Government should finally face up to the question of â€˜British kinshipâ€™ and should realise that â€˜the old Commonwealth is quite simply an extension of the British race overseasâ€™.</p>

